      prompt: `<div>The kinetic energy K, in joules, of an object is given by the formula K = (1/2)mv&sup2;, where m is the mass, in kilograms, and v is the velocity, in meters per second. If the kinetic energy of a certain object can be found using the formula K = 98v&sup2;, what is the mass, in kilograms, of the object?</div>`,
